Perl6 also has optional typing:<p><pre><code>  sub fib (Int $n) returns Void {
    my Int ($a, $b) = 0, 1;
    while $a < $n {
      say $a;
      ($a, $b) = ($b, $a + $b);
    }
  }
</code></pre>
NB. At moment <i>Void</i> doesn't appear to be implemented in current version of Rakudo.  Removing <i>returns Void</i> will make it work!
